eu.planets_project.TB.interfaces.data.model
Interface Objectives

All Superinterfaces:
BenchmarkObjectivesHandle
public interface Objectives
extends BenchmarkObjectivesHandle

The use of an Objective object will normally be split up into two stages. 1. First in the ExperimentSetup a set of given objectives are choosen and each's focus for this experiment is chosen 2. In the ExperimentAnalysis these selected benchmarks are filled in with values. To-Do: It still needs clarification whether additional benchmarking objectives may get added in the analysis phase or if the set should be final after the setup phase.
